'''Liam Patrick Kelly''' (born 23 January 1996) is a Scottish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{Scottish football updater|Rangers}} club [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] and the [[Scotland national football team|Scotland national team]]. Kelly has previously played for [[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]], [[East Fife F.C.|East Fife]], [[Livingston F.C.|Livingston]] and [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]].

==Club career==
===Rangers===
Kelly joined Rangers aged ten and played in the club's youth sides, notably scoring the final penalty during Rangers under-17s [[Glasgow Cup]] win in 2012.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.eveningtimes.co.uk/news/13233159.Goalkeeper_Liam_Kelly_is_the_hero_as_Rangers_colts_triumph_in_Glasgow_Cup_penalty_shoot_out/ |title=Goalkeeper Liam Kelly is the hero as Rangers colts triumph in Glasgow Cup penalty shoot-out |date=17 April 2012 |work=Evening Times |publisher=Herald & Times Group |location=Glasgow}}</ref><ref name="glasgow">{{Cite news |last=Dickson |first=Andrew |url=http://rangers.co.uk/news/academy-news/gers-win-glasgow-cup/ |title=Gers Win Glasgow Cup |date=16 April 2012 |work=Rangers.co.uk |access-date=17 April 2012 |publisher=Rangers Football Club}}</ref>

After training with the first-team for the majority of the 2014–15 season and featuring on the bench, Kelly signed a contract extension on 25 February 2015, until the summer of 2018.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.rangers.co.uk/news/academy-news/item/8567-kelly-delight-at-new-deal |title=Kelly Delight At New Deal |date=25 February 2015 |work=Rangers.co.uk |access-date=16 July 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150712115838/http://www.rangers.co.uk/news/academy-news/item/8567-kelly-delight-at-new-deal |archive-date=12 July 2015 |publisher=Rangers Football Club}}</ref>

====Loan moves====
On 8 January 2016, Kelly joined [[East Fife F.C.|East Fife]] in [[Scottish League Two]] on a six-month loan.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://rangers.co.uk/news/headlines/kelly-joins-east-fife/? |title=Kelly Joins East Fife |date=8 January 2016 |work=Rangers.co.uk |publisher=Rangers Football Club}}</ref> During his time at [[Bayview Stadium]], Kelly played in 16 league matches and was part of the side which won the League Two title.<ref name="East fife">{{Cite news |last=Macgregor |first=Archie |url=http://www.scotsman.com/sport/football/competitions/league-two/clyde-0-0-east-fife-league-2-title-joy-for-fifers-1-4102467 |title=Clyde 0-0 East Fife: League 2 title joy for Fifers |date=16 April 2016 |work=[[The Scotsman]] |publisher=Johnston Press |location=Edinburgh}}</ref> Upon returning to Rangers, Kelly travelled to the United States with the first team for a pre-season training camp.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://rangers.co.uk/news/headlines/gers-head-america/ |title=Gers head to America |date=27 June 2016 |work=Rangers.co.uk |publisher=Rangers Football Club}}</ref> However, on 15 July 2016, he was loaned out to the then [[Scottish League One]] team [[Livingston F.C.|Livingston]] until January 2017.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Thomson |first=Nick |url=http://rangers.co.uk/news/headlines/kelly-moves-loan/? |title=Kelly Moves On Loan |date=15 July 2016 |work=Rangers.co.uk |publisher=Rangers Football Club}}</ref> He made his debut for ''Livi'' the next day in a [[Scottish League Cup|League Cup]] match against [[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=McLauchlin |first=Brian |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36753147 |title=Livingston 2-3 St Mirren |date=16 July 2016 |work=BBC Sport |publisher=BBC}}</ref>

===Livingston===
Kelly moved to [[Livingston F.C.|Livingston]], where he had previously been on loan, for an undisclosed fee in June 2018.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://rangers.co.uk/news/club/liam-kelly-joins-livingston/ |title=Liam Kelly Joins Livingston |date=8 June 2018 |publisher=Rangers FC |access-date=8 June 2018}}</ref> He played regularly for Livingston in the 2018–19 season, but then invoked a release clause in his contract.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48519001 |title=Liam Kelly triggers Livingston release clause amid English Championship interest |date=4 June 2019 |publisher=BBC Sport |access-date=5 June 2019}}</ref>

===Queens Park Rangers===
On 14 June 2019, Kelly signed for [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]] for an undisclosed fee on a four-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48639859 |title=Liam Kelly: QPR sign goalkeeper from Livingston |date=14 June 2019 |publisher=BBC Sport |access-date=14 June 2019}}</ref> It was reported that the transfers fee was £50,000 with Livingston retaining a sell on bonus.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/local-sport/livingston-goalkeeper-liam-kelly-completes-16517652|title=Livingston goalkeeper Liam Kelly completes switch to Queen's Park Rangers|first=Callum|last=Carson|date=14 June 2019|website=Daily Record}}</ref> He made his debut on 13 August 2019, in an [[EFL Cup]] match against [[Bristol City F.C.|Bristol City]] saving two penalties in a 5–4 penalty shootout win.

====Motherwell (loan)====
On 6 January 2021, Kelly moved on loan to [[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]] for the remainder of the season.<ref>{{cite web|title=Liam Kelly signs on loan|url=https://www.motherwellfc.co.uk/2021/01/06/liam-kelly-signs-on-loan/|website=motherwellfc.co.uk|date=6 January 2021|accessdate=6 January 2021}}</ref>

===Motherwell===
On 5 July 2021, Kelly returned to Motherwell on a permanent transfer from Queens Park Rangers, signing a three-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |title=LIAM KELLY RETURNS TO MOTHERWELL |url=https://www.motherwellfc.co.uk/2021/07/05/liam-kelly-returns-to-motherwell/ |website=motherwellfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Motherwell F.C. |access-date=5 July 2021 |date=5 July 2021}}</ref>

===Return to Rangers===
On 27 June 2024, Rangers completed the signing of goalkeeper Liam Kelly on a two-year deal. Kelly, a former Rangers academy player, returned to Ibrox after his contract expired at Motherwell.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rangers.co.uk/Article/rangers-sign-scotland-international-goalkeeper-liam-kelly/6V1RhVAM3lxTWnYRogJ7bR |title=Rangers Sign Scotland International Goalkeeper Liam Kelly |date=27 June 2024 |publisher=Rangers FC |access-date=27 June 2024}}</ref> Kelly made his first competitive appearance for Rangers on 21 December 2024, in a 1&ndash;0 victory against [[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]] at [[Ibrox Stadium|Ibrox]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sports/articles/c05p87r1ny9o |title=Kelly revels in 'unbelievable' Rangers debut |date=22 December 2024 |publisher=BBC Sport |access-date=3 July 2025}}{{dead link|date=September 2025|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> He then started in an [[Old Firm]] game for the first time, as Rangers won 3&ndash;0 against [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] on 2 January 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rangers.co.uk/fixture/rangers-vs-celtic-scottish-premiership-2025-01-02/2B2XDvamYVuay2C5Ay281w |title=Rangers 3-0 Celtic |date=2 January 2025 |publisher=Rangers FC |access-date=13 January 2025}}</ref> Following a dip of form for regular starter Butland, Kelly was chosen to play in a [[2024&ndash;25 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] tie against [[Athletic Bilbao]]. He saved a [[penalty kick]] in the first leg, which ended in a goalless draw.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/ckgeyng3dnlt |first=Martin |last=Dowden |title=Rangers 0-0 Athletic Club - Liam Kelly saves penalty for 10-man hosts |website=BBC Sport |date=10 April 2025 |accessdate=2 July 2025}}</ref> Kelly played in 10 league games during the [[2024&ndash;25 Scottish Premiership|2024&ndash;25]] season, recording four clean sheets.

==International career==
[[File:Украина U-21 - Шотландия U-21 4-0. 6 сентября 2016 года — 708159.jpg|thumb|Kelly (No 1) with [[Scotland national under-21 football team|Scotland U21s]] in Ukraine, 2016]]
Kelly has represented Scotland at various age levels, up to an including the [[Scotland national under-21 football team|under-21]] team.<ref name="SFA" />

Kelly received his first call-up to the senior [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] squad in March 2019 for games against [[Kazakhstan national football team|Kazakhstan]] and [[San Marino national football team|San Marino]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/47604868 |title=Scotland: Andy Robertson to miss Kazakhstan clash as trio also pull out |date=17 March 2019 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=18 March 2019 |publisher=BBC}}</ref> After many call-ups to the squad without playing, Kelly finally made his full international debut in a [[friendly match|friendly]] against [[France national football team|France]] on 17 October 2023.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/67061897 |title=France 4-1 Scotland: Star-studded hosts inflict heavy defeat on makeshift Scots |website=BBC Sport |date=17 October 2023 |accessdate=17 October 2023}}</ref> He was selected in the Scotland squads for [[UEFA Euro 2024]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/clwwdq8dzrno |title=Liam Kelly signs short-term Motherwell deal to secure Euro bonus |website=BBC Sport |date=8 June 2024 |accessdate=8 June 2024}}</ref> and the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/scotland-craig-gordon-2026-fifa-world-cup-roster|title=Scotland Includes 43-year-old Goalkeeper Craig Gordon In World Cup Squad|publisher=Fox Sports}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cvgz2e8g4e8o|title=World Cup: Meet the Scotland squad in their own words|last=Canavan|first=Amy|date=3 June 2026|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

==Style of play==
[[Kenny Miller]], who played alongside Kelly at Rangers and was also his player-manager at Livi, said of him in 2018: "He's excellent with the ball at his feet. He's a proper modern-day goalkeeper".<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45741014 |title=Liam Kelly 'could lead next batch of Scotland goalkeepers' - Kenny Miller |date=4 October 2018 |work=BBC Sport |access-date=4 October 2018 |publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation}}</ref>

==Personal life==
He is the brother of [[Livingston F.C.|Livingston]] defender [[Sean Kelly (Scottish footballer)|Sean Kelly]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Sean Kelly says Liam Kelly 'has the ability and mindset' to play for Rangers|url=https://sportslens.com/sean-kelly-says-liam-kelly-has-the-ability-and-mindset-to-play-for-rangers/251805/|website=Sports Lens|author=Charlie Rhodes |date=25 November 2018}}</ref> and [[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]] goalkeeper Shay Kelly.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Clarke |first=Fraser |date=2025-03-30 |title=My brother is a Rangers ace - now I've made my SPFL debut I want to follow him |url=https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/brother-rangers-ace-now-ive-34960489 |access-date=2026-01-03 |website=Daily Record |language=en}}</ref> In October 2023 Liam and Sean faced each other from 12 yards in a Scottish Premiership fixture, with Sean scoring his penalty past Liam.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/local-sport/motherwell-kid-lennon-miller-wise-31148552|title=Motherwell kid Lennon Miller has wise head on his shoulders, red card won't affect him, says skipper|last=McGilvray|first=Andy|date=10 October 2023|work=Daily Record}}</ref>

